OL,7,FMs Blythyn was asked if she accepted
OL,8,Fthe concerns of the unions on (the
OL,9,Fappointment of Mr Millington) and
OL,10,Freplied: "The decision needed to be
OL,11,Ftaken on an operational basis for an
OL,12,Finterim chief fire officer for
OL,13,Foperational needs and I'm sure the
OL,14,Fchief fire advisor can advise on the
OL,15,Frationale behind that.
OL,17,F"It was a decision for our
OL,18,Fcommissioners to take and we are
OL,19,Flooking to recruit a substantive chief
OL,20,Ffire officer as soon as possible.
